WEBVTT

00:00.001 --> 00:02.768
[OLIVER]: <i>PREVIOUSLY,</i>
<i>ON </i> SIGNED, SEALED, DELIVERED--

00:02.770 --> 00:05.237
SHE'S FROM THE U.S.P.S.
IN WASHINGTON, D.C.

00:05.239 --> 00:07.172
I IMAGINE
WE HAVE DIFFERING NOTIONS

00:07.174 --> 00:08.640
ON WHAT CONSTITUTES "FUN."

00:08.642 --> 00:10.676
I HAVE NO DOUBT THAT WE DO.

00:10.678 --> 00:13.112
WAIT TILL I TELL YOU ABOUT OLIVER.

00:13.114 --> 00:14.546
IT WAS VERY UNGENTLEMANLY OF ME

00:14.548 --> 00:15.714
TO REMAIN HERE WHERE I COULD

00:15.716 --> 00:17.182
OVERHEAR YOUR CONVERSATION.

00:17.184 --> 00:18.384
I WON'T SAY A WORD.

00:20.353 --> 00:22.421
[♪]

00:31.231 --> 00:33.632
[♪]

00:38.338 --> 00:40.672
I REALLY CAN'T STALL THEM ANYMORE.

00:42.475 --> 00:43.475
SORRY!

00:44.744 --> 00:46.779
SORRY! [PANTING]

00:48.248 --> 00:50.182
[EXHALES SHAKILY]

00:51.184 --> 00:52.651
I GOT IT!

00:57.123 --> 00:59.091
IF SOMETHING HAPPENS--

00:59.093 --> 01:00.325
NOTHING'S GONNA HAPPEN.

01:00.327 --> 01:01.326
PROMISE.

01:03.096 --> 01:04.730
YOU HAVE TO MAIL THIS.

01:04.732 --> 01:07.199
DO IT FOR MICHAEL AND OUR LITTLE GIRL.

01:08.301 --> 01:09.268
[DEEP, WRACKING WHEEZING]

01:10.737 --> 01:12.771
[MONITOR FLATLINING]
[NURSE]: I NEED YOUR HELP HERE!

01:12.773 --> 01:14.306
DEEP BREATHS.

01:14.308 --> 01:15.607
[COUGHS]

01:15.609 --> 01:18.110
MOVE IT!
LET'S GO. LET'S GO!

01:18.112 --> 01:21.180
OKAY! HANG IN THERE, MELISSA.
HANG IN THERE! HANG IN THERE!

01:21.182 --> 01:22.748
[BEEPING]

01:22.750 --> 01:24.183
WE'RE NOT GETTING A PULSE.

01:24.185 --> 01:25.851
PRESSURE'S DROPPING.

01:25.853 --> 01:28.320
-MORE SUCTION.
-SHE'S DESATTING, 70%.

01:28.322 --> 01:29.321
-COME ON, MELISSA!
-WE'RE LOSING HER!

01:29.323 --> 01:32.191
-65%!
-MORE SUCTION!

01:32.193 --> 01:34.426
[STEADY TONE BEEPING]

01:34.428 --> 01:36.295
[FLATLINE BLARING]

01:39.566 --> 01:42.167
[♪]

01:48.374 --> 01:50.609
[♪]

02:05.758 --> 02:07.392
[CANDY-STRIPER, KIM]:
MORNING.

02:07.394 --> 02:08.760
WOULD YOU LIKE TO SEE
ANY MAGAZINES TODAY?

02:10.330 --> 02:12.764
YOU KNOW, ALL MY JOHN GRISHAMS
HAVE BEEN CHECKED OUT,

02:12.766 --> 02:15.634
BUT HOLD ON, LET ME SEE.

02:18.671 --> 02:20.906
[♪]

02:20.908 --> 02:23.175
[GASPS]

02:26.479 --> 02:29.314
♪ SEND ME LOVE EVERY DAY

02:29.316 --> 02:31.683
♪ AND SEND ME ON MY WAY

02:31.685 --> 02:35.654
♪ DELIVER ME
JUST DELIVER ME ♪

02:40.226 --> 02:42.528
SO, WHEN WE WERE TALKING
ABOUT OLIVER THE OTHER DAY,

02:42.530 --> 02:43.662
HE WAS SITTING RIGHT BEHIND US?

02:43.664 --> 02:45.564
MM. BUT IT WASN'T HIS FAULT.

02:45.566 --> 02:46.899
HE WANTED TO LEAVE,

02:46.901 --> 02:49.301
HE JUST DIDN'T WANT TO STAND UP AND EMBARRASS YOU.

02:49.303 --> 02:51.370
WHAT DID I SAY?

02:51.372 --> 02:53.172
WHAT DID I SAY?

02:53.174 --> 02:54.806
-ALL NICE THINGS. YOU KNOW--
-OH--

02:54.808 --> 02:57.576
...HOW HE'S A NICE GUY,
HE GOES TO CHURCH,

02:57.578 --> 02:58.911
HE'S GENEROUS, CONSIDERATE--

02:58.913 --> 03:00.479
[GIGGLES]
HE NEEDS A SENSE OF HUMOR.

03:00.481 --> 03:01.480
NO.

03:01.482 --> 03:02.915
NO... NO!

03:02.917 --> 03:05.817
I CAN'T GO BACK
TO THE DEAD LETTER OFFICE NOW.

03:05.819 --> 03:08.287
TAKE ME BACK TO WASHINGTON
WITH YOU, PLEASE?

03:08.289 --> 03:09.288
NO!

03:09.290 --> 03:10.822
THIS PLACE IS GOOD FOR YOU.

03:10.824 --> 03:13.458
BESIDES, I CAN'T GO BACK EITHER.

03:13.460 --> 03:15.394
NOT UNTIL I FULFILL
MY SPECIAL PROJECTS QUOTA.

03:15.396 --> 03:16.728
[MORTIFIED SIGH]

03:16.730 --> 03:17.729
OH.

03:19.365 --> 03:20.532
[BACKGROUND CHATTER]

03:20.534 --> 03:21.967
BE COOL.

03:21.969 --> 03:23.468
HE'S COMING OVER.

03:23.470 --> 03:24.536
BUT DON'T LET HIM KNOW
I TOLD YOU.

03:24.538 --> 03:26.238
WHAT DO I DO?
WHAT DO I SAY?

03:26.240 --> 03:27.338
I MEAN, HE WOULD DIE

03:27.340 --> 03:28.874
IF HE KNEW THAT YOU KNEW
THAT HE KNEW THAT--

03:28.876 --> 03:30.709
GOOD MORNING, MS. McINERNEY,
MS. STARKWELL,

03:30.711 --> 03:32.678
I WAS HOPING TO FIND YOU HERE. AGAIN.

03:32.680 --> 03:35.247
GOSH, OLIVER. IT'S SO GOOD TO SEE YOU.

03:35.249 --> 03:36.648
WE WERE JUST SITTING HERE

03:36.650 --> 03:39.718
TALKING ABOUT... NOTHING.

03:39.720 --> 03:42.387
UM, TRYING TO FIND A TOPIC, AND...

03:42.389 --> 03:43.655
[SHANE SIGHS]

03:43.657 --> 03:44.823
OH, FORGET ABOUT IT.

03:44.825 --> 03:45.991
WHAT'S GOING ON?

03:45.993 --> 03:47.392
OH, UH, WELL, WE RECEIVED

03:47.394 --> 03:49.528
A RATHER UNUSUAL PACKAGE THIS MORNING.

03:49.530 --> 03:52.664
I'D LIKE TO CONSULT WITH YOU
AND-- A-AND YOU, PERHAPS,

03:52.666 --> 03:54.399
MS. STARKWELL, IF YOU'RE INTERESTED.

03:54.401 --> 03:55.767
YES, I'M ALWAYS INTERESTED,

03:55.769 --> 03:57.536
BUT I HAVE A PROBLEM I HAVE TO FIX

03:57.538 --> 03:59.838
IN "PARCELS" AT 9:00.

03:59.840 --> 04:01.840
APPARENTLY, EVEN IF IT FITS, IT AIN'T SHIPPING.

04:01.842 --> 04:03.375
MM. AT LEAST NOT TO KAZAKHSTAN.

04:03.377 --> 04:04.576
[CHUCKLES]

04:04.578 --> 04:06.378
BUT KEEP ME POSTED? HUH?

04:06.380 --> 04:08.347
[CHUCKLING]

04:09.515 --> 04:11.316
AW, I LOVE HER.

04:11.318 --> 04:13.885
IT MUST BE NICE
HAVING A FRIEND

04:13.887 --> 04:15.587
VISITING FROM
YOUR OLD STOMPING GROUNDS.

04:15.589 --> 04:18.523
YEAH. ALTHOUGH I REALLY DIDN'T
STOMP THAT MUCH.

04:18.525 --> 04:19.925
I DIDN'T STAY THERE THAT LONG.

04:19.927 --> 04:22.461
OH, I SEE.

04:22.463 --> 04:25.864
SO SHOULD WE EXPECT YOU TO...

04:25.866 --> 04:27.299
MOVE ON AT SOME POINT?

04:27.301 --> 04:29.368
"ON"?

04:29.370 --> 04:31.336
ARE YOU UNHAPPY AT THE D.L.O.?

04:31.338 --> 04:33.505
WITH... US?

04:34.540 --> 04:36.575
"US"?

04:36.577 --> 04:37.576
THE TEAM. UH...

04:37.578 --> 04:39.444
NORMAN, RITA...

04:39.446 --> 04:41.446
OH! NO. NO.

04:41.448 --> 04:42.981
NOT UNHAPPY.

04:42.983 --> 04:46.885
IN FACT, I'M ACTUALLY STARTING
TO DO A LITTLE STOMPING HERE.

04:48.488 --> 04:52.424
AH. I'M SURE NORMAN AND RITA
WILL BE VERY HAPPY TO HEAR THAT.

04:52.426 --> 04:55.360
THEY ADMIRE YOU AND YOUR REMARKABLE...

04:55.362 --> 04:57.929
MY REMARKABLE...?

04:57.931 --> 05:01.466
UH... ABILITY TO, UH...

05:01.468 --> 05:03.402
EMBRACE...

05:03.404 --> 05:05.370
A CHALLENGE SUCH AS THIS.

05:05.372 --> 05:07.439
[AWKWARD CHUCKLE] AH.

05:07.441 --> 05:09.408
IT ARRIVED,
ADDRESSED DIRECTLY

05:09.410 --> 05:11.777
TO THE DEAD LETTER OFFICE.

05:14.947 --> 05:16.848
-OH, A BIBLE?
-MM-HMM.

05:16.850 --> 05:17.949
AND, UH...

05:17.951 --> 05:19.651
THIS WAS INCLUDED.

05:21.754 --> 05:24.022
THE COVER LETTER READS, UH,

05:24.024 --> 05:25.657
"DEAR POST OFFICE--

05:25.659 --> 05:27.057
"AFTER MANY YEARS OF TREATMENT,

05:27.059 --> 05:30.529
"A PATIENT OF OURS AT LONG OAKS
LODGE FOR MENTAL HEALTH

05:30.531 --> 05:32.964
"HAS RECOVERED ENOUGH
TO LEAVE OUR FACILITY.

05:32.966 --> 05:34.733
"AT THE TIME HE LEFT, HE
CONFESSED TO US THAT THE BIBLE

05:34.735 --> 05:36.535
"HE HAD CARRIED SO LONG WAS, IN FACT,

05:36.537 --> 05:38.370
"STOLEN BY HIM

05:38.372 --> 05:40.505
"APPROXIMATELY 10 YEARS AGO.

05:40.507 --> 05:42.441
"INSIDE THAT BIBLE WAS AN UNMAILED LETTER,

05:42.443 --> 05:45.410
"WHICH OUR PATIENT DECORATED AND USED AS A BOOKMARK.

05:45.412 --> 05:47.713
"WE ARE SENDING YOU BOTH

05:47.715 --> 05:49.081
"IN HOPES THAT YOU MIGHT FORWARD THEM

05:49.083 --> 05:50.349
"TO THEIR RIGHTFUL OWNERS.

05:50.351 --> 05:51.516
"THANK YOU.

05:51.518 --> 05:52.651
"NANCY GRAY,

05:52.653 --> 05:54.653
"DIRECTOR OF
PSYCHIATRIC SERVICES,

05:54.655 --> 05:56.355
LONG OAKS
LODGE FOR MENTAL HEALTH."

05:56.357 --> 05:58.957
[♪]

06:00.793 --> 06:02.494
UH...

06:02.496 --> 06:04.963
IT'S MICHAEL W-H-E-- SOMETHING,

06:04.965 --> 06:07.666
2234... SOMETHING, D-E-N-V...

06:07.668 --> 06:08.800
WELL, IT MUST BE DENVER.

06:08.802 --> 06:10.102
MM-HMM. UH...

06:10.104 --> 06:11.803
MOST OF IT'S NOT LEGIBLE.

06:11.805 --> 06:13.071
RETURN ADDRESS SAYS

06:13.073 --> 06:15.640
"ST. AUGUSTO HOSPITAL INTENSIVE CARE UNIT."

06:15.642 --> 06:18.510
37-CENT 2004 COMMEMORATIVE.

06:18.512 --> 06:20.145
IT, UH, LACKS POSTMARK, HOWEVER.

06:20.147 --> 06:23.048
OH. THE STAMP SUGGESTS INTENTION TO MAIL.

06:23.050 --> 06:26.084
AND WE MUST HONOUR THAT INTENTION.

06:26.086 --> 06:28.086
VERY GOOD, MS. MCINERNEY.

06:32.425 --> 06:33.558
ALRIGHT.

06:35.695 --> 06:37.763
HERE WE ARE.

06:40.900 --> 06:42.534
AHEM.

06:44.570 --> 06:45.937
SHAKY HANDWRITING.

06:45.939 --> 06:48.006
UH, "MAY 16, 2004.

06:48.008 --> 06:49.107
"DEAR MICHAEL...

06:49.109 --> 06:51.042
"I CAN EXPLAIN EVERYTHING.

06:51.044 --> 06:52.778
"IT'S NOT WHAT YOU THINK.

06:52.780 --> 06:54.846
"I DON'T BLAME YOU FOR WALKING OUT,

06:54.848 --> 06:57.416
"BUT I CAN'T LET THEM OPERATE ON ME

06:57.418 --> 06:59.050
"UNLESS I KNOW, IF I DIE...

06:59.052 --> 07:01.586
AT LEAST YOU HAVE THE TRUTH."

07:02.622 --> 07:04.456
"MY HEAD HURTS

07:04.458 --> 07:07.092
AND I CAN'T REMEMBER MUCH ABOUT YESTERDAY..."

07:10.029 --> 07:11.897
THANK YOU, SIR.
I APPRECIATE YOUR CONFIDENCE.

07:11.899 --> 07:12.998
MIKE, ISN'T THAT YOUR WIFE?

07:13.000 --> 07:15.634
[BACKGROUND CHATTER]

07:18.538 --> 07:21.773
UH...

07:23.676 --> 07:24.676
HEY.

07:24.678 --> 07:25.911
HEY!

07:27.847 --> 07:29.181
WHAT-- WHAT ARE
YOU DOING HERE?

07:29.183 --> 07:30.849
THE PARTNERS TOOK ME TO LUNCH.

07:30.851 --> 07:32.150
THEY'RE GONNA SUPPORT ME IN THE CAMPAIGN.

07:33.486 --> 07:35.454
DID-- DID I MENTION?
HE'S REALLY GONNA RUN.

07:35.456 --> 07:38.156
I ALWAYS KNEW YOU'D RUN THE WORLD SOMEDAY.

07:39.592 --> 07:41.626
SOME THINGS NEVER CHANGE, I GUESS.

07:42.628 --> 07:44.463
[♪]

07:44.465 --> 07:46.698
I JUST, UH--

07:46.700 --> 07:49.968
HEY.
HEY-HEY-HEY-HEY-HEY...

07:49.970 --> 07:53.505
I KNOW WHAT YOU'RE THINKING, BUT YOU'RE WRONG.

07:53.507 --> 07:54.505
OH, I'M SORRY,

07:54.507 --> 07:56.041
IT'S JUST I SEE MY WIFE AND HER OLD BOYFRIEND

07:56.043 --> 07:57.142
TOGETHER AT A HOTEL.

07:57.144 --> 07:58.210
I DON'T KNOW WHAT TO MAKE OF IT.

07:58.212 --> 08:00.045
HAVE YOU EVER NOTICED,

08:00.047 --> 08:01.746
WHEN THINGS ARE GOOD,
HE'S YOUR BEST FRIEND,

08:01.748 --> 08:03.114
BUT AS SOON AS WE'RE HAVING PROBLEMS,

08:03.116 --> 08:04.816
HE'S MY "EX-BOYFRIEND"?

08:04.818 --> 08:06.084
BARRY AND I WERE HAVING LUNCH.

08:06.086 --> 08:08.854
THAT'S ALL THAT HAPPENED.
LUNCH.

08:08.856 --> 08:10.622
I DIDN'T SEE YOU IN THE RESTAURANT.

08:10.624 --> 08:11.723
MICHAEL,

08:11.725 --> 08:14.793
PLEASE, JUST TRUST ME ON THIS.

08:14.795 --> 08:15.994
I'LL TELL YOU ALL ABOUT IT

08:15.996 --> 08:17.162
WHEN ABBY AND I GET BACK FROM THE TRIP.

08:17.164 --> 08:19.097
RIGHT.

08:19.099 --> 08:21.600
WHY DON'T YOU COME?

08:21.602 --> 08:23.101
NO.

08:23.103 --> 08:25.737
TAKE SOME MOTHER/DAUGHTER TIME.

08:25.739 --> 08:26.905
WE NEED SOME HUSBAND/WIFE TIME.

08:26.907 --> 08:29.741
I GOTTA GO.

08:29.743 --> 08:31.643
[MELISSA, WRITING]:
<i>"I WOULD HAVE NEVER LET YOU WALK AWAY</i>

08:31.645 --> 08:33.512
IF I HAD KNOWN WHAT WAS COMING."

08:33.514 --> 08:35.814
[FRIEND]: SHE SAID IT ALL HAPPENED SO FAST.

08:35.816 --> 08:37.249
ONE SECOND, THEY WERE ALL LAUGHING,

08:37.251 --> 08:39.117
AND THE NEXT THING THEY KNEW, THEY HIT THE ROCKS,

08:39.119 --> 08:40.919
AND EVERYONE WAS IN THE WATER--

08:40.921 --> 08:42.087
MR. WHEELER?

08:42.089 --> 08:43.588
YES?

08:43.590 --> 08:45.190
WE JUST GOT THE LAB WORK BACK ON YOUR BLOOD.

08:45.192 --> 08:46.791
I'M AFRAID THERE'S AN ISSUE.

08:50.096 --> 08:52.898
[♪]

08:56.569 --> 08:58.270
MICHAEL...

09:03.142 --> 09:05.277
HOW'S ABBY?

09:06.712 --> 09:08.947
THEY THINK SHE'S GONNA LOSE A KIDNEY.

09:08.949 --> 09:11.016
[GASPS] OH, NO.

09:11.018 --> 09:14.052
NO...

09:14.054 --> 09:15.654
SHE NEEDED BLOOD.

09:15.656 --> 09:17.656
SO...

09:17.658 --> 09:20.292
I GAVE THEM MINE.

09:20.294 --> 09:23.128
BUT MY BLOOD DIDN'T MATCH.

09:24.697 --> 09:26.798
MICHAEL, WAIT. LISTEN TO ME.

09:26.800 --> 09:29.034
WHAT A FOOL I AM.

09:29.036 --> 09:31.069
I MEAN, ABBY WAS
BORN, WHAT--?

09:31.071 --> 09:33.872
NINE MONTHS AND TWO DAYS AFTER WE GOT MARRIED.

09:33.874 --> 09:37.609
MAYBE, IF YOU AND BARRY HADN'T
BEEN MESSING AROUND ON FRIDAY,

09:37.611 --> 09:38.743
I WOULD'VE BEEN UP THERE WITH YOU GUYS,

09:38.745 --> 09:39.978
AND OUR LITTLE GIRL

09:39.980 --> 09:41.646
WOULDN'T BE FIGHTING FOR HER LIFE RIGHT NOW!

09:41.648 --> 09:42.781
LISTEN TO ME,
MI-- MICHAEL.

09:42.783 --> 09:43.848
CORRECTION--

09:43.850 --> 09:45.951
YOUR LITTLE GIRL.

09:45.953 --> 09:46.952
MICHAEL!

09:46.954 --> 09:49.654
MICHAEL...

09:49.656 --> 09:50.989
[WEAKLY]: MICHAEL!

09:52.058 --> 09:54.292
[GASPS AND SOBS]

09:54.294 --> 09:55.827
[KNOCKS] CANDY STRIPER.

09:55.829 --> 09:58.897
CAN I GET YOU A MAGAZINE OR ANYTHING?

09:58.899 --> 10:01.132
[MELISSA, WRITING]:
<i>"IT'S TRUE, MICHAEL.</i>

10:01.134 --> 10:03.735
<i>YOU'RE NOT THE FATHER OF ABBY."</i>

10:03.737 --> 10:06.237
<i>"IT'S A TERRIBLE SECRET I'VE KEPT ALL THIS TIME</i>

10:06.239 --> 10:07.939
<i>"BECAUSE I LOVE YOU</i>

10:07.941 --> 10:10.208
<i>"AND I ONLY WANTED THE BEST FOR BOTH OF YOU.</i>

10:10.210 --> 10:12.177
<i>"THE TRUTH IS...</i>

10:12.179 --> 10:14.913
<i>BARRY ISN'T THE FATHER, EITHER."</i>

10:16.983 --> 10:19.784
"THERE HASN'T BEEN ANYTHING
BETWEEN ME AND BARRY SINCE..."

10:21.087 --> 10:22.721
"COLLEGE,

10:22.723 --> 10:24.189
"AND WE WERE AT THE CLAIREMONT ON FRIDAY

10:24.191 --> 10:25.389
"BECAUSE WE WERE PLANNING

10:25.391 --> 10:27.993
"A SURPRISE PARTY FOR YOUR BIRTHDAY NEXT WEEK.

10:27.995 --> 10:30.962
IF YOU DON'T BELIEVE ME, ASK THE CATERER."

10:30.964 --> 10:33.198
ALRIGHT.

10:33.200 --> 10:36.034
WELL, ALL WE HAVE TO DO
IS CALL THE CLAIREMONT HOTEL,

10:36.036 --> 10:38.003
ASK THEM TO CHECK THEIR RECORDS FOR A BIRTHDAY PARTY

10:38.005 --> 10:39.337
THAT WAS CANCELED

10:39.339 --> 10:42.741
FOR A MICHAEL W-H-SOMETHING IN MAY OF 2004.

10:42.743 --> 10:44.142
WHO'S THE FATHER?

10:44.144 --> 10:46.244
[SCOFFS] YOU AMAZE ME.

10:46.246 --> 10:48.113
AN HOUR AGO, YOU DIDN'T
KNOW THESE PEOPLE EXISTED.

10:48.115 --> 10:49.681
NOW YOU CAN'T CONTINUE

10:49.683 --> 10:51.983
UNTIL YOU DETERMINE THE PARENTAGE OF THEIR CHILD.

10:51.985 --> 10:53.752
I-I CAN'T EXPLAIN IT, OLIVER.

10:53.754 --> 10:55.920
I JUST...
HAVE GOT AN INSTINCT.

10:56.956 --> 10:58.823
AN INSTINCT.

10:58.825 --> 11:02.360
YOU ONCE SAID,
"WE DON'T FIND THE LETTERS, THEY FIND US."

11:02.362 --> 11:03.695
I DO.

11:03.697 --> 11:04.796
WELL, THIS MORNING,

11:04.798 --> 11:06.765
I WOKE UP WITH A DISTINCT FEELING

11:06.767 --> 11:08.933
THAT TODAY WOULD POSE A UNIQUE CHALLENGE.

11:08.935 --> 11:10.201
WAS THAT A FEELING

11:10.203 --> 11:11.369
OR A FORTUNE COOKIE, MS. MCINERNEY?

11:11.371 --> 11:14.239
[GROANS] OH.
JUST... KEEP READING.

11:14.241 --> 11:15.807
OLIVER, PLEASE?

11:15.809 --> 11:17.842
BESIDES...

11:17.844 --> 11:19.244
EVERYBODY KNOWS THAT HOTELS

11:19.246 --> 11:21.212
DESTROY THEIR RECORDS AFTER 10 YEARS.

11:21.214 --> 11:23.214
NOW YOU'RE JUST MAKING THINGS UP.

11:26.185 --> 11:28.820
ON THE OTHER HAND,

11:28.822 --> 11:31.456
I DO HAVE A FEELING ABOUT THIS, TOO.

11:31.458 --> 11:32.724
WHAT'S YOUR INSTINCT?

11:32.726 --> 11:34.693
NOT AN INSTINCT.

11:35.761 --> 11:37.062
MORE OF A SIGN, REALLY.

11:39.265 --> 11:40.365
THIS PAGE...

11:41.901 --> 11:43.902
THE ENVELOPE
WAS BOOKMARKING...

11:43.904 --> 11:46.337
"AND YOU WILL KNOW THE TRUTH,

11:46.339 --> 11:49.074
AND THE TRUTH WILL MAKE YOU FREE."

11:49.076 --> 11:50.475
10 YEARS IS A LONG TIME

11:50.477 --> 11:53.445
TO BE A PRISONER TO A LIE, MS. MCINERNEY.

11:59.151 --> 12:01.352
"YOU ARE NOT ABBY'S FATHER,

12:01.354 --> 12:03.221
NEITHER IS BARRY."

12:03.223 --> 12:04.823
[MELISSA, WRITING]:
<i>"DO YOU REMEMBER</i>

12:04.825 --> 12:06.291
<i>"THE NIGHT BEFORE WE GOT MARRIED?"</i>

12:06.293 --> 12:07.759
[LIPS SMACKING]

12:08.861 --> 12:11.029
I CAN'T WAIT.
MARRY ME NOW.

12:11.031 --> 12:12.731
[SHE CHUCKLES]

12:14.300 --> 12:15.867
[KNOCK ON WINDOW]

12:15.869 --> 12:17.435
ALRIGHT, GUYS. BREAK IT UP.

12:17.437 --> 12:20.405
SHE'S YOURS TOMORROW, MICHAEL BUT SHE'S OURS TONIGHT!

12:20.407 --> 12:21.873
HAVE FUN.

12:21.875 --> 12:23.808
-BYE.
-BYE.

12:27.179 --> 12:28.313
[BLOWS A KISS]

12:31.183 --> 12:34.819
[MELISSA]:
<i>"IT STARTED AS UST ONE LAST GIRLS' NIGHT OUT."</i>

12:34.821 --> 12:35.987
THIS ONE'S FOR WHEN

12:35.989 --> 12:37.055
MICHAEL WINS HIS FIRST ELECTION.

12:37.057 --> 12:39.190
[CHUCKLES]

12:39.192 --> 12:41.192
OH! [LAUGHING]

12:41.194 --> 12:43.027
UH, WAIT A MINUTE.

12:43.029 --> 12:45.330
MAYBE IT'LL BE ME THAT GOES INTO POLITICS!

12:45.332 --> 12:46.464
WE THOUGHT OF THAT!

12:46.466 --> 12:48.133
AND THEN...

12:48.135 --> 12:50.301
"HELLO, MICHAEL!"

12:50.303 --> 12:52.937
[WOMEN LAUGHING]

12:52.939 --> 12:54.539
[♪]

12:56.942 --> 12:57.976
[WOMAN]: IT'S THE THOUGHT THAT COUNTS.

12:57.978 --> 12:59.377
[MELISSA]: ABSOLUTELY. CHEERS.

12:59.379 --> 13:00.879
[ALL LAUGHING]

13:00.881 --> 13:02.847
[GLASSES CLINKING]

13:04.817 --> 13:06.050
I'LL BE RIGHT BACK.

13:06.052 --> 13:07.185
OKAY.

13:07.187 --> 13:09.554
IT'S DOWNSTAIRS, IN THE BACK.

13:09.556 --> 13:12.457
<i>"I DON'T REMEMBER EVERYTHING, MICHAEL,</i>

13:12.459 --> 13:15.326
<i>BUT I KNOW HE SAID HE WAS GONNA KILL ME."</i>

13:16.829 --> 13:19.531
<i>"EXCEPT HE DIDN'T.</i>

13:19.533 --> 13:22.333
<i>"BUT THAT NIGHT...</i>

13:22.335 --> 13:24.402
<i>I WANTED TO DIE JUST THE SAME."</i>

13:25.838 --> 13:27.472
[ALL LAUGHING]

13:28.874 --> 13:31.843
[♪]

13:31.845 --> 13:32.977
WELL...

13:35.080 --> 13:37.315
MS. MCINERNEY, YOU WERE RIGHT.

13:41.053 --> 13:43.254
AS MUCH AS I WISH THAT WEREN'T TRUE.

13:44.490 --> 13:47.325
[♪]

13:53.833 --> 13:56.367
THIS IS THE SADDEST LETTER I'VE EVER READ.

13:56.369 --> 13:59.003
[SHANE]: THAT'S WHAT REBECCA SAID WHEN SHE READ IT.

13:59.005 --> 14:02.073
SHE WANTS A REPORT
ON OUR PROGRESS BY TOMORROW.

14:02.075 --> 14:03.408
DO WE HAVE ENOUGH TO FIGURE IT OUT?

14:03.410 --> 14:04.576
NOT YET.

14:04.578 --> 14:05.977
I CAN'T FIND

14:05.979 --> 14:07.946
ANY POLICE REPORTS FROM AN O'HANNIGAN'S BAR

14:07.948 --> 14:09.047
FROM THAT YEAR.

14:09.049 --> 14:10.281
I DON'T THINK YOU WILL.

14:10.283 --> 14:12.417
IT WAS NEVER REPORTED.

14:12.419 --> 14:14.552
"I DECIDED THAT I WAS NEVER GOING--"

14:14.554 --> 14:16.287
[MELISSA, OVERLAPPING]:
<i>"...GOING TO TELL A SOUL</i>

14:16.289 --> 14:19.190
<i>WHAT HAPPENED, SO..."</i>

14:19.192 --> 14:21.626
-[SNIFFLING]
-  <i>"I MADE IT THROUGH THE WEDDIG</i>

14:21.628 --> 14:24.929
<i>WITH LOTS OF MAKEUP AND CHAMPAGNE."</i>

14:24.931 --> 14:26.564
<i>"A FEW DAYS LATER,</i>

14:26.566 --> 14:29.300
<i>"I SAW HIS FACE IN</i> THE DENVER CITY PRESS.

14:29.302 --> 14:31.169
<i>"HE USED A GUN BEFORE,</i>

14:31.171 --> 14:32.637
<i>"TO ASSAULT A KINDERGARTEN TEACHER</i>

14:32.639 --> 14:33.972
<i>"THREE DAYS BEFORE ME.</i>

14:33.974 --> 14:36.107
<i>"THEY CAUGHT HIM FOR THAT,</i>

14:36.109 --> 14:38.509
<i>AND HE WENT TO PRISON FOR LIFE."</i>

14:40.079 --> 14:42.347
"IN FACT, IT WAS THE LAST CASE

14:42.349 --> 14:44.182
"THAT TOMMY BOYLEN PROSECUTED

14:44.184 --> 14:46.885
"BEFORE HE WAS APPOINTED TO THE BENCH, REMEMBER?

14:46.887 --> 14:51.322
"BUT EVEN THOUGH HE'S BEEN IN JAIL ALL THIS TIME,

14:51.324 --> 14:53.324
"I CAN'T STOP THINKING ABOUT HIM...

14:53.326 --> 14:56.227
AND THERE'S ALWAYS ABBY TO REMIND ME."

14:56.229 --> 14:57.962
OH, DEAR.

14:57.964 --> 15:01.199
"I THOUGHT A THOUSAND TIMES
ABOUT NOT GOING THROUGH WITH IT,

15:01.201 --> 15:03.067
BUT-- BUT I COULDN'T..."

15:03.069 --> 15:05.103
[RITA'S BREATH SHAKING]

15:07.406 --> 15:09.440
"BECAUSE, IN THE END,

15:09.442 --> 15:11.643
"IT DIDN'T MATTER WHO HER FATHER WAS.

15:11.645 --> 15:13.945
"ALL THAT MATTERED

15:13.947 --> 15:15.947
WAS WHO HER FATHER WAS GOING TO BE."

15:17.316 --> 15:18.549
I'M SORRY.

15:20.286 --> 15:21.486
[OLIVER EXHALES HEAVILY]

15:21.488 --> 15:23.187
"IT'S TRUE, MICHAEL,

15:23.189 --> 15:24.689
"YOU'RE NOT ABBY'S FATHER,

15:24.691 --> 15:26.357
"BUT YOU ARE, AND YOU WILL ALWAYS BE,

15:26.359 --> 15:27.959
"HER DADDY.

15:27.961 --> 15:29.527
"PLEASE FORGIVE ME.

15:29.529 --> 15:31.930
"AND IF YOU CAN'T, I UNDERSTAND.

15:31.932 --> 15:34.432
BUT I HAVE ALWAYS LOVED YOU..."

15:35.634 --> 15:38.336
"AND I'VE BEEN BLESSED TO BE YOUR WIFE."

15:38.338 --> 15:40.271
[OTHERS SNIFFING]

15:40.273 --> 15:43.007
"LOVE, MELISSA."

15:44.977 --> 15:45.976
[SIGHING]

15:47.079 --> 15:50.214
MICHAEL WANTED TO BE IN POLITICS.

15:50.216 --> 15:53.151
MELISSA CALLS THE PROSECUTOR "TOMMY,"

15:53.153 --> 15:56.321
AS IF THEY WERE SOMEHOW
FRIENDLY WITH THE D.A.'S OFFICE.

15:56.323 --> 15:58.589
I BELIEVE THAT WE ARE DEALING
WITH AN OFFICER OF THE COURT.

15:58.591 --> 16:00.491
I CAN RUN A LIST OF LAWYERS

16:00.493 --> 16:02.360
FROM THE COLORADO BAR ASSOCIATION

16:02.362 --> 16:05.396
WHOSE NAMES START WITH "W-H-E" AND THEN--

16:05.398 --> 16:09.500
OH. WHEATON, WHEEMS, WHEELER, WHELCHER.

16:09.502 --> 16:11.102
WELL, ACTUALLY, THERE'S TWO WHELCHERS

16:11.104 --> 16:13.504
RITA, YOU REALLY ARE AMAZING.

16:13.506 --> 16:15.139
YOU KNOW THAT?

16:15.141 --> 16:16.407
OLIVER?

16:16.409 --> 16:18.109
YES, NORMAN?

16:18.111 --> 16:20.645
DO YOU THINK I COULD, UM,
HAVE ONE OF YOUR YOO-HOOS?

16:20.647 --> 16:22.113
OF COURSE.

16:22.115 --> 16:23.581
I THINK
WE COULD ALL USE ONE.

16:25.084 --> 16:28.119
OKAY, MICHAEL WHEELER, AGE 45,

16:28.121 --> 16:30.722
DEPUTY DISTRICT ATTORNEY, DENVER, SINCE 2006.

16:30.724 --> 16:32.490
HE IS THE FATHER OF ONE,

16:32.492 --> 16:34.592
AND WAS WIDOWED IN 2004.

16:34.594 --> 16:36.294
[HITS KEY]

16:36.296 --> 16:38.429
[PRINTER WHIRS]

16:42.067 --> 16:44.068
THIS IS HIS ADDRESS.

16:46.005 --> 16:47.105
OLIVER...

16:47.107 --> 16:49.073
I'M TORN ABOUT THIS.

16:49.075 --> 16:51.275
THIS IS AN INCREDIBLY DIFFICULT LETTER

16:51.277 --> 16:52.677
TO DELIVER.

16:52.679 --> 16:54.746
YES. IT IS.

16:59.418 --> 17:01.519
I WONDER WHAT A DIFFERENCE

17:01.521 --> 17:03.788
SENDING THIS WILL MAKE AFTER ALL THIS TIME.

17:03.790 --> 17:06.090
GOD ONLY KNOWS, RITA.

17:09.361 --> 17:11.262
[STAMP CLACKS]

17:11.264 --> 17:13.064
BUT THAT'S ENOUGH FOR ME.

17:14.099 --> 17:16.734
[♪]

17:16.736 --> 17:18.703
[CHUTE WHOOSHES]

17:24.576 --> 17:27.078
[♪]

17:29.148 --> 17:32.784
RITA? HOW MANY STORES IN PUEBLO
BEGIN WITH THE LETTER "Z"?

17:32.786 --> 17:34.685
OH, WELL, THERE'S ZIP'S SKATEBOARDS,

17:34.687 --> 17:36.554
WHICH IS 456 SOUTH EXPOSITION.

17:36.556 --> 17:39.223
OH, WAIT! NO. IT'S NOT. IT'S, UM...

17:39.225 --> 17:40.691
[RITA SIGHS]

17:40.693 --> 17:42.460
UH, 5614.

17:42.462 --> 17:45.063
I AM SO SORRY. I CAN'T CONCENTRATE.

17:45.065 --> 17:46.431
NEITHER CAN I.

17:46.433 --> 17:49.067
IS EVERYBODY THINKING WHAT I'M THINKING?

17:49.069 --> 17:50.234
ABOUT MELISSA...

17:50.236 --> 17:51.636
AND ABBY...

17:51.638 --> 17:53.438
AND MICHAEL?

17:53.440 --> 17:54.605
TO BE HONEST, MS. MCINERNEY,

17:54.607 --> 17:56.541
I'M TRYING NOT TO THINK ABOUT IT.

17:56.543 --> 17:59.243
[♪]

18:00.412 --> 18:01.813
I AM...

18:01.815 --> 18:04.115
GOING TO GO GET SOME COFFEE.

18:05.484 --> 18:08.486
YOU KNOW, I COULD GO FOR
A LARGE AMERICANO WITH...

18:10.722 --> 18:12.457
I DON'T THINK SHE'S GOING TO GET COFFEE.

18:13.792 --> 18:16.327
YES. I'M TOUGH ON CRIME,

18:16.329 --> 18:17.829
AND I HAVE REALLY GOOD REASON TO BE.

18:17.831 --> 18:19.397
HER NAME IS--

18:19.399 --> 18:21.532
"IT'S MY DAUGHTER, HER NAME IS--"

18:22.601 --> 18:23.734
IT'S MY DAUGHTER.

18:23.736 --> 18:25.770
HER NAME IS ABBY.

18:25.772 --> 18:27.205
AND I ASK YOU,

18:27.207 --> 18:29.807
WHAT ARE THE NAMES OF THE ONES THAT YOU LOVE?

18:29.809 --> 18:32.577
THE PEOPLE THAT YOU EXPECT
OUR CITY TO SERVE AND PROTECT?

18:32.579 --> 18:34.712
[CHUCKLES]:
THAT'S GOOD, BUT...

18:34.714 --> 18:35.880
DON'T LOOK SO SEVERE, DAD.

18:35.882 --> 18:38.316
YOU HAVE TO SMILE HEN YOU SAY THAT.

18:38.318 --> 18:42.153
YOU GONNA BE MY DOCTOR
OR MY CAMPAIGN MANAGER?

18:44.523 --> 18:46.491
[♪]

18:55.134 --> 18:56.667
MAY I HELP YOU?

18:56.669 --> 18:57.867
YES! HELLO.

18:57.869 --> 19:01.772
I AM FROM THE UNITED STATES POSTAL SERVICE.

19:01.774 --> 19:04.475
I AM CONDUCTING A ROUTINE EVALUATION OF...

19:04.477 --> 19:06.511
MAIL.

19:06.513 --> 19:08.346
HOW IT'S GOING HERE?

19:08.348 --> 19:10.448
WELL, IT STILL COMES IN EVERY DAY.

19:10.450 --> 19:11.582
EXCUSE ME A MOMENT.

19:11.584 --> 19:13.551
MM-HMM.

19:13.553 --> 19:15.520
[♪]

19:17.523 --> 19:19.323
NOW, I THOUGHT YOU WERE GONNA SHAVE.

19:19.325 --> 19:20.858
BEARDS MAKE VOTERS THINK

19:20.860 --> 19:22.627
CANDIDATE HAVE SOMETHING TO HIDE.

19:22.629 --> 19:24.562
I'LL TAKE THAT INTO CONSIDERATION.

19:24.564 --> 19:26.464
[LAUGHS]
SPOKEN LIKE A POLITICIAN.

19:26.466 --> 19:29.233
THANKS
FOR DOING THIS.

19:29.235 --> 19:30.535
IT WAS NICE TO BE ASKED.

19:32.538 --> 19:34.839
SO... WHAT ARE YOU UP TO?

19:34.841 --> 19:36.307
NOT MUCH.

19:36.309 --> 19:37.642
UH, WENT IN FOR SOME TESTS WITH DR. ACKERMAN

19:37.644 --> 19:39.377
AND SIMON AND I HAVE JUST BEEN...

19:39.379 --> 19:40.478
TESTS?

19:40.480 --> 19:41.679
HOW ARE YOU FEELING?

19:41.681 --> 19:42.747
FINE.

19:44.416 --> 19:46.617
SIMON AND I ARE STUDYING FOR MEDCATS.

19:46.619 --> 19:48.319
"SIMON"?

19:48.321 --> 19:49.554
BOYFRIEND?

19:49.556 --> 19:50.788
YOU MET HIM AND YOU LIKED HIM.

19:50.790 --> 19:52.723
MM-HMM.

19:52.725 --> 19:55.193
[♪]

19:55.195 --> 19:57.628
WOW.

19:57.630 --> 19:59.730
LOOK AT THIS LETTER.

19:59.732 --> 20:00.965
IT'S 10 YEARS OLD.

20:00.967 --> 20:02.767
WE GET LOTS OF OLD CASES.

20:02.769 --> 20:06.237
NO, I MEAN THE POST OFFICE
SAYS IT'S BEEN LOST THAT LONG.

20:07.506 --> 20:09.774
[♪]

20:17.849 --> 20:20.418
WHAT? WHO'S IT FROM?

20:20.420 --> 20:21.419
UM...

20:21.421 --> 20:23.754
NOBODY.

20:23.756 --> 20:25.790
OKAY. [CHUCKLES]

20:25.792 --> 20:28.292
WELL, SEE YA, DAD.

20:28.294 --> 20:29.694
BYE, SWEETHEART. I LOVE YOU.

20:29.696 --> 20:30.828
-I LOVE YOU.
-OKAY.

20:30.830 --> 20:33.731
[♪]

20:36.969 --> 20:38.869
NOW, HOW CAN I HELP YOU?

20:38.871 --> 20:40.871
WELL, AS I WAS SAYING--

20:40.873 --> 20:42.340
-SANDRA?
-YEAH?

20:42.342 --> 20:43.708
I'M TAKING AN EARLY LUNCH.

20:43.710 --> 20:45.376
OKAY.

20:47.713 --> 20:49.380
I'M SORRY.

20:49.382 --> 20:51.249
WRONG ZIP CODE.

20:52.985 --> 20:55.286
[♪]

21:16.808 --> 21:19.510
[♪]

21:31.757 --> 21:34.392
[BREAKS INTO SOBS]

21:40.332 --> 21:43.000
[WEEPING]

21:43.002 --> 21:44.935
OH, GOD!

21:44.937 --> 21:47.805
OH, I'M SORRY, MEL.

21:50.542 --> 21:52.543
[SNIFFS, THEN ROARS]:
I WILL KILL HIM!

21:54.980 --> 21:57.415
[MICHAEL SOBBING UNCONTROLLABLY]

21:59.017 --> 22:01.585
[♪]

22:06.425 --> 22:08.459
[QUIETLY]:
I WILL KILL HIM.

22:09.594 --> 22:11.629
[♪]

22:13.065 --> 22:14.332
MS. MCINERNEY.

22:14.334 --> 22:16.567
THAT CERTAINLY WAS A LOT OF COFFEE.

22:16.569 --> 22:19.403
OLIVER, I THINK MICHAEL WHEELER IS OUT FOR REVENGE.

22:19.405 --> 22:21.539
[♪]

22:23.809 --> 22:25.409
HE'S GOING TO KILL THAT MAN?

22:25.411 --> 22:26.444
HE SAID HE WOULD.

22:26.446 --> 22:27.478
HOW DO YOU KNOW THIS?

22:27.480 --> 22:29.347
IT'S A LONG STORY.

22:29.349 --> 22:31.615
I'LL SKIP THE PART WHERE
I FOLLOWED HIM INTO A CEMETERY.

22:31.617 --> 22:33.651
-OH, BOY.
-ANYBODY WHO DOESN'T--

22:33.653 --> 22:34.885
...WANT TO KNOW WHAT I'M ABOUT TO DO

22:34.887 --> 22:36.053
SHOULD LEAVE NOW.

22:36.055 --> 22:37.353
WELL, I DON'T WANT TO KNOW,

22:37.355 --> 22:39.090
AND I'M NOT LEAVING,
AND YOU'RE GONNA TELL ME ANYWAY.

22:39.092 --> 22:40.725
LET'S JUST SAY

22:40.727 --> 22:42.526
I AM TAKING MY COMPUTER SKILLS TO A WHOLE NEW LEVEL.

22:42.528 --> 22:44.695
[KEYS CLACKING]

22:44.697 --> 22:47.398
[♪]

22:51.570 --> 22:54.071
[SIGHS HEAVILY]

23:00.712 --> 23:02.480
HE'S SEARCHING THE KINDERGARTEN TEACHER'S STORY,

23:02.482 --> 23:03.614
JUST THE WAY I DID.

23:03.616 --> 23:04.682
HOW DO YOU KNOW THIS?

23:04.684 --> 23:06.751
I BROKE INTO THE CITY HALL MAINFRAME.

23:06.753 --> 23:08.018
OH, WOW.

23:08.020 --> 23:09.920
NOW YOU SEE WHY
WASHINGTON HATED TO LOSE ME.

23:09.922 --> 23:12.056
[OLIVER SIGHS]

23:12.058 --> 23:14.458
[♪]

23:29.141 --> 23:30.508
[CLICKING]

23:31.610 --> 23:34.011
[♪]

23:36.014 --> 23:37.548
WHAT'S HE DOING?

23:37.550 --> 23:38.916
SEARCHING THE D.A.'S FILES.

23:38.918 --> 23:40.851
HE PROBABLY WANTS TO FIND OUT
AS MUCH ABOUT BRACKNER

23:40.853 --> 23:42.420
BEFORE HE KILLS HIM.

23:42.422 --> 23:44.020
NOW, WHAT ON EARTH WOULD MAKE YOU THINK

23:44.022 --> 23:45.689
MR. WHEELER WOULD KILL A MAN
WHO'S ALREADY IN JAIL?

23:45.691 --> 23:46.824
I WATCHED HIM READ THE LETTER.

23:46.826 --> 23:48.926
I SAW HIM STAND OVER MELISSA'S GRAVE

23:48.928 --> 23:51.929
AND SWEAR THAT HE WOULD KILL BRACKNER.

23:51.931 --> 23:53.164
PROBABLY WITH THE SIG SAUER

23:53.166 --> 23:54.932
THAT HE HAS REGISTERED
AS A CONCEALED WEAPON.

23:54.934 --> 23:57.034
BUT I THOUGHT BRACKNER WAS

23:57.036 --> 23:58.436
SUPPOSED TO BE IN JAIL FOR LIFE.

23:58.438 --> 23:59.603
SO DID MICHAEL.

23:59.605 --> 24:02.473
WAIT! IT LOOKS LIKE HE'S ONTO SOMETHING.

24:10.215 --> 24:11.682
[OLIVER]: I DON'T UNDERSTAND.

24:11.684 --> 24:13.150
BRACKNER MAY BE RELEASED?

24:13.152 --> 24:14.718
IT'S TRUE.

24:14.720 --> 24:16.921
BRACKNER'S ON HIS LAST APPEAL,

24:16.923 --> 24:18.189
BUT THIS TIME, DEFENSE SAYS

24:18.191 --> 24:20.891
THEY'VE GOT ENOUGH FOR A REVERSAL,

24:20.893 --> 24:22.091
BASED ON NEW FORENSICS

24:22.093 --> 24:24.695
SUGGESTING A COMPROMISE
IN THE CHAIN OF EVIDENCE.

24:24.697 --> 24:26.530
THERE'S AN OLD ILLINOIS PRECEDENT FROM 1898

24:26.532 --> 24:27.531
ON MATERIAL EVIDENCE.

24:27.533 --> 24:28.666
I'LL EMAIL IT TO YOU.

24:28.668 --> 24:31.068
GREAT. THANKS.

24:31.070 --> 24:32.570
UH...

24:32.572 --> 24:34.905
YOU KNOW, I THOUGHT YOU'D BE, UH,

24:34.907 --> 24:36.240
TOO BUSY CAMPAIGNING

24:36.242 --> 24:38.142
TO PAY ATTENTION TO THIS LITTLE STUFF.

24:38.144 --> 24:40.711
PUTTING TRASH LIKE THIS AWAY

24:40.713 --> 24:41.846
IS WORTH WHATEVER IT TAKES.

24:45.484 --> 24:47.685
HEY, YOU MIND IF I DROP BY AND WATCH?

24:49.221 --> 24:51.255
YOU'RE THE BOSS.

24:52.624 --> 24:55.192
[♪]

24:56.595 --> 24:57.962
BUT THAT'S
JUST NOT FAIR!

24:57.964 --> 24:59.663
I'M BETTING THAT'S WHERE MICHAEL'S GONNA DO IT--

24:59.665 --> 25:01.732
IN COURT, AT THE APPEAL.

25:01.734 --> 25:03.567
BECAUSE IF BRACKNER GETS RELEASED,

25:03.569 --> 25:04.702
HE'LL DISAPPEAR.

25:04.704 --> 25:05.936
I DON'T LIKE THE IDEA

25:05.938 --> 25:07.571
OF THAT GUY WALKING AROUND.

25:07.573 --> 25:10.040
BUT, HEY! WHAT IF HE COULDN'T WALK?

25:10.042 --> 25:11.575
YOU KNOW, I HAVE A COUSIN--

25:11.577 --> 25:13.844
NORMAN, ENOUGH REGULATIONS
HAVE BEEN BROKEN ALREADY.

25:15.947 --> 25:17.581
WE DON'T KNOW ANY MORE THAN MR. WHEELER.

25:17.583 --> 25:18.916
PROBABLY FAR LESS.

25:18.918 --> 25:20.851
BESIDES, WHAT IF-- WHAT IF WE'RE WRONG?

25:20.853 --> 25:21.952
WHAT IF WE ARE RIGHT?

25:21.954 --> 25:23.687
HIS DAUGHTER HAS LOST ENOUGH ALREADY.

25:23.689 --> 25:25.689
SHE HAS. I JUST--

25:25.691 --> 25:27.258
WAIT A MINUTE.

25:27.260 --> 25:29.627
MS. MCINERNEY,

25:29.629 --> 25:31.028
WHAT WAS THE NAME OF HER DOCTOR AGAIN?

25:31.030 --> 25:32.963
ACKERMAN!

25:32.965 --> 25:34.532
WE'VE GOT THE NAME.

25:34.534 --> 25:36.233
I'LL JUST LOOK UP THE RECORDS.

25:39.271 --> 25:42.740
WHOA... OKAY.

25:42.742 --> 25:44.642
THIS IS A GAME-CHANGER.

25:44.644 --> 25:45.843
I-I CAN'T BELIEVE OU FOUND IT.

25:45.845 --> 25:47.678
YOU'RE RIGHT. SOMEONE HAS TO STOP HIM.

25:47.680 --> 25:49.880
YEAH, BUT WE CAN'T PROVE IT.
AT LEAST NOT IN TIME.

25:49.882 --> 25:51.015
OLIVER,
YOU ALWAYS SAY

25:51.017 --> 25:52.716
THAT WE HAVE
TO BE RESPONSIBLE

25:52.718 --> 25:54.685
FOR WHAT LITTLE TRUTH
THAT WE HAVE.

25:54.687 --> 25:57.187
WE HAVE IT NOW,
AND MICHAEL DOESN'T.

25:57.189 --> 25:59.056
WE HAVE A MORAL OBLIGATION TO STOP HIM.

25:59.058 --> 26:00.691
WE'LL DO EVERYTHING IN OUR POWER,

26:00.693 --> 26:02.159
BUT OUR POWERS ARE SOMEWHAT LIMITED.

26:02.161 --> 26:03.160
HOW LIMITED?

26:03.162 --> 26:04.862
WELL, WE HAVE TO STAY

26:04.864 --> 26:06.864
WITHIN SOME PRETTY STRICT
GUIDELINES AROUND HERE.

26:06.866 --> 26:08.766
AND, YOU KNOW,
EVERY ONCE IN A WHILE,

26:08.768 --> 26:10.167
WHEN NO ONES'S LOOKING,

26:10.169 --> 26:12.703
WE PUSH THE ENVELOPE
IF IT'S IMPORTANT.

26:12.705 --> 26:15.973
WELL, I THINK THIS IS ONE OF THOSE TIMES

26:15.975 --> 26:18.175
AND I'M CERTAINLY NOT LOOKING.

26:18.177 --> 26:19.743
THERE YOU GO.

26:19.745 --> 26:21.312
YOU HEARD IT DIRECT FROM THE HEAD OF SPECIAL PROJECTS

26:21.314 --> 26:22.947
IN WASHINGTON, D.C.

26:22.949 --> 26:24.181
IT IS A TEMPTING PROPOSITION,

26:24.183 --> 26:26.050
BUT WE ARE TALKING ABOUT SAVING A LIFE HERE.

26:26.052 --> 26:27.818
TWO, ACTUALLY.

26:27.820 --> 26:29.787
WE'RE GONNA NEED A LOT MORE THAN
SOMEONE LOOKING THE OTHER WAY.

26:29.789 --> 26:32.656
WE'RE GONNA NEED FULL AUTHORITY TO PULL THIS OFF.

26:32.658 --> 26:33.691
AT LEAST TEMPORARILY.

26:33.693 --> 26:36.060
WHY SHOULD IT BE TEMPORARY?

26:37.329 --> 26:38.596
MS. MCINERNEY...

26:38.598 --> 26:40.297
TAKE A LETTER.

26:41.600 --> 26:45.169
"MEMO FOR GENERAL DISTRIBUTION

26:45.171 --> 26:47.071
"FROM THE UNITED STATES POST OFFICE, WASHINGTON D.C.

26:47.073 --> 26:49.640
"EFFECTIVE IMMEDIATELY,

26:49.642 --> 26:51.942
"THE DIVISION OF SPECIAL PROJECTS

26:51.944 --> 26:54.078
"ANNOUNCES THE REORGANIZATION

26:54.080 --> 26:56.914
OF THE DENVER BRANCH OF THE D.L.O. INTO..."

26:56.916 --> 26:58.182
UH... INTO A...

26:58.184 --> 26:59.316
A SPECIAL TASK FORCE?

26:59.318 --> 27:01.118
AH! THAT'S GOOD.

27:01.120 --> 27:02.219
GOOD, GOOD, GOOD, GOOD.

27:02.221 --> 27:04.054
"...INTO A SPECIAL TASK FORCE,

27:04.056 --> 27:07.992
"DEDICATED TO THE DELIVERY OF SENSITIVE LETTERS,

27:07.994 --> 27:11.662
"PACKAGES, AND RELATED MATERIALS

27:11.664 --> 27:14.331
DEEMED 'UNDELIVERABLE'
AND NEEDING SPECIAL HANDLING."

27:14.333 --> 27:16.200
REBECCA, THAT'S GREAT,

27:16.202 --> 27:17.400
BUT I CAN'T HELP BUT THINK

27:17.402 --> 27:20.738
THAT WE MIGHT NEED A LITTLE MORE LATITUDE.

27:20.740 --> 27:22.306
AN EXPENSE ACCOUNT, FLEXIBLE HOURS...

27:22.308 --> 27:24.808
TRAVEL.

27:24.810 --> 27:26.343
OKAY. GOT IT.
GOT IT.

27:26.345 --> 27:30.714
"SAID TASK FORCE SHALL BE GIVEN
WIDE POWERS OF DISCRETION,

27:30.716 --> 27:32.082
"FISCAL INDEPENDENCE,

27:32.084 --> 27:33.684
"AND...

27:33.686 --> 27:37.021
SHALL REPORT DIRECTLY AND SOLELY TO THIS DIVISION."

27:38.056 --> 27:39.223
LOVE IT!

27:39.225 --> 27:41.025
I'M SORRY.

27:41.027 --> 27:42.860
W-WHAT JUST HAPPENED?

27:42.862 --> 27:44.328
I JUST FOUND MY SPECIAL PROJECT.

27:44.330 --> 27:47.698
[LAUGHS]
AND YOU GUYS JUST GOT PROMOTED.

27:48.800 --> 27:51.201
NORMAN IS GOING TO LOVE THIS.

27:52.971 --> 27:54.338
SO...

27:54.340 --> 27:56.840
WE'RE A SECRET BRANCH OF THE POST OFFICE NOW?

27:56.842 --> 27:58.308
NOT SECRET.

27:58.310 --> 28:00.678
JUST A VERY, VERY SPECIAL TASK FORCE.

28:00.680 --> 28:02.713
BUT, I MEAN...
WOW, WOW! WOW!

28:02.715 --> 28:04.081
THIS IS SO EXCITING!

28:04.083 --> 28:06.784
WE ARE LIKE, UH, LIKE SECRET AGENTS OR SUPERHEROES.

28:06.786 --> 28:08.752
WE'RE GONNA NEED A NAME, LIKE, UH,

28:08.754 --> 28:10.721
LIKE A REAL NAME, LIKE "THE A-TEAM".

28:10.723 --> 28:12.022
OR THE "IMPOSSIBLE MISSIONS FORCE,"

28:12.024 --> 28:13.724
OR, UH, "SEAL TEAM SIX"--

28:13.726 --> 28:14.925
"THE INCREDIBLES"?

28:14.927 --> 28:17.761
A MONIKER, SOME SORT OF UNIQUE DESIGNATION.

28:17.763 --> 28:19.363
WAIT! I'VE GOT IT!

28:22.167 --> 28:24.368
"THE POSTABLES."

28:24.370 --> 28:25.269
HUH.

28:25.271 --> 28:27.037
THE POSTABLES.

28:27.039 --> 28:28.772
RIGHT? THE POSTABLES!
OH, MY GOSH.

28:28.774 --> 28:30.340
WE COULD EVEN HAVE JACKETS!

28:30.342 --> 28:32.843
-OR PATCHES. -"POSTABLE" PATCHES!

28:32.845 --> 28:34.344
I THINK YOU SHOULD DRAW THE LINE AT CAPES.

28:34.346 --> 28:36.146
WILL DO.

28:36.148 --> 28:38.849
WELL, I'M PROUD TO BE A POSTABLE.

28:38.851 --> 28:41.485
[♪]

28:41.487 --> 28:42.486
[CLAP]

28:44.389 --> 28:45.923
[MICHAEL]:
OF COURSE. YEAH.

28:45.925 --> 28:47.491
SHE'S FROM, UH,

28:47.493 --> 28:50.027
THREE HILLS, WYOMING, IF YOU CAN BELIEVE THAT.

28:50.029 --> 28:51.261
IT'S A VERY SMALL TOWN.

28:51.263 --> 28:53.363
YEAH. HER NAME'S EARTHA LEWIS.

28:53.365 --> 28:55.432
I DON'T HAVE THE SPELLING--

28:55.434 --> 28:56.500
IF HE HAD A GUN,

28:56.502 --> 28:58.068
HE WOULDN'T TAKE IT THROUGH SECURITY.

28:58.070 --> 28:59.269
JUST, SORRY--

28:59.271 --> 29:01.338
[SHANE]:
I SCANNED HIS BANK RECORDS.

29:01.340 --> 29:02.638
HE CLOSED ALL OF HIS ACCOUNTS

29:02.640 --> 29:03.974
AND PUT A POWER OF ATTORNEY
INTO HIS DAUGHTER'S NAME

29:03.976 --> 29:05.442
IN CASE ANYTHING HAPPENS.

29:05.444 --> 29:09.012
[NORMAN]: MM. HE DID HAVE
AN AWFULLY BIG BREAKFAST.

29:09.014 --> 29:10.414
I'M TELLING YOU,

29:10.416 --> 29:11.982
HE'S NOT EXPECTING TO GET OUT OF HERE.

29:11.984 --> 29:13.083
AT LEAST, NOT AS A FREE MAN.

29:13.085 --> 29:14.384
OH, MR. WHEELER.

29:14.386 --> 29:16.954
FORGOT YOUR BRIEFCASE.

29:16.956 --> 29:18.388
THANKS, ANTHONY.

29:19.958 --> 29:21.358
AND HE JUST GOT HIS BRIEFCASE

29:21.360 --> 29:23.927
THROUGH SECURITY WITHOUT INSPECTION.

29:23.929 --> 29:26.230
[QUIETLY EXHALING]

29:26.232 --> 29:29.466
[♪]

29:40.545 --> 29:42.279
[EXHALES NERVOUSLY]

29:42.281 --> 29:44.314
DID I MISS ANYTHING?

29:46.184 --> 29:47.351
ALL RISE.

29:50.922 --> 29:53.323
[♪]

29:58.930 --> 30:00.964
IN THE MATTER OF THE STATE OF COLORADO

30:00.966 --> 30:02.833
VERSUS CARL BRACKNER,

30:02.835 --> 30:04.501
I AM PREPARED TO DELIVER MY DECISION

30:04.503 --> 30:06.804
AFTER I HAVE CONFERRED WITH COUNSEL.

30:06.806 --> 30:08.105
PLEASE APPROACH THE BENCH.

30:08.107 --> 30:11.074
[♪]

30:15.814 --> 30:18.148
WOULD YOU MIND PUTTING
YOUR BRIEFCASE ON THE FLOOR,

30:18.150 --> 30:20.017
UNDER HERE?

30:20.019 --> 30:22.419
IT'S JUST THAT I'M--
I'M ALLERGIC TO, UM, LEATHER.

30:22.421 --> 30:25.289
NO, I'M SORRY. I NEED IT WITH ME RIGHT NOW.

30:25.291 --> 30:28.592
OH. SURE.

30:28.594 --> 30:30.427
ACHOO.

30:33.364 --> 30:35.299
[ATTORNEY SIGHS]

30:35.301 --> 30:37.167
DEFENSE FILED A MOTION

30:37.169 --> 30:40.971
TO DENY THE 1898 RULING ON MATERIAL EVIDENCE.

30:40.973 --> 30:43.473
SHE SAYS I CAN'T CITE A CASE THAT OLD

30:43.475 --> 30:46.009
UNLESS I CAN PROVE RELEVANCE.

30:46.011 --> 30:47.211
YOU GOT ANY IDEAS?

30:47.213 --> 30:48.445
WELL, YOU COULD--

30:48.447 --> 30:50.614
SHE'S QUESTIONING RELEVANCE

30:50.616 --> 30:52.149
BECAUSE IT'S A HUNDRED YEARS OLD?

30:52.151 --> 30:54.852
THAT'S EXACTLY <i>WHY </i> IT'S RELEVANT!

30:54.854 --> 30:56.987
JUDGES WROTE DECISIONS A HUNDRED YEARS AGO

30:56.989 --> 30:59.423
SO WE COULD HEAR THEIR VOICES TODAY.

30:59.425 --> 31:01.091
IF WE DON'T LISTEN TO THEIR PAST,

31:01.093 --> 31:02.426
THEN WHO WILL LISTEN

31:02.428 --> 31:05.362
TO THIS JUDGE'S DECISION
A HUNDRED YEARS FROM NOW?

31:05.364 --> 31:06.864
YEAH!
NOT TO MENTION

31:06.866 --> 31:08.899
THE STATE OF ILLINOIS VS. PRESTON

31:08.901 --> 31:11.935
CITED THE SAME CASE IN 1989 AND PREVAILED,

31:11.937 --> 31:13.537
UPHOLDING THE PREVIOUS VERDICT

31:13.539 --> 31:15.339
OF 1977.

31:18.309 --> 31:20.277
YOUR HONOUR?

31:20.279 --> 31:21.445
MAY I APPROACH?

31:21.447 --> 31:24.047
[♪]

31:24.049 --> 31:26.283
WHO ARE YOU PEOPLE?

31:26.285 --> 31:28.118
MR. WHEELER.

31:28.120 --> 31:31.255
WE KNOW WHAT'S IN THAT LETTER IN YOUR POCKET.

31:31.257 --> 31:33.290
WE KNOW WHAT'S IN YOUR BRIEFCASE.

31:33.292 --> 31:36.460
AND I BELIEVE WE KNOW WHAT'S ON YOUR MIND.

31:36.462 --> 31:38.362
BELIEVE ME, I WOULDN'T BLAME YOU

31:38.364 --> 31:41.431
IF YOU STUFFED CARL BRACKNER
INTO A BLENDER AND HIT "FRAPPE."

31:43.401 --> 31:45.135
BUT WE HAVE INFORMATION

31:45.137 --> 31:47.604
ABOUT YOUR DAUGHTER

31:47.606 --> 31:48.904
THAT WILL CONVINCE YOU

31:48.906 --> 31:50.440
OF THE TERRIBLE MISTAKE YOU'RE ABOUT TO MAKE.

31:50.442 --> 31:52.376
YOU MUST BELIEVE ME.

31:52.378 --> 31:54.044
THERE IS ONLY ONE COURSE OF ACTION

31:54.046 --> 31:55.479
YOU CAN TAKE TODAY.

31:55.481 --> 31:56.546
YOU MUST TRADE US YOUR BRIEFCASE AND THE--

31:56.548 --> 31:58.348
SIG SAUER P229.

31:58.350 --> 32:01.251
...THAT'S CONCEALED INSIDE.

32:02.453 --> 32:04.688
READ THE INFORMATION, DECIDE FOR YOURSELF.

32:06.057 --> 32:08.292
YOU MUST TRUST US.

32:08.294 --> 32:10.527
THIS IS A MATTER OF LIFE AND DEATH.

32:10.529 --> 32:12.696
[♪]

32:15.366 --> 32:17.668
PLEASE, MR. WHEELER.

32:19.938 --> 32:22.639
[♪]

32:31.950 --> 32:34.251
WELL DONE, SIR.
THANK YOU.

32:37.488 --> 32:39.990
[♪]

32:47.565 --> 32:49.366
[OLIVER]:
SIR, IF WE DON'T ACT NOW,

32:49.368 --> 32:51.268
YOU WON'T BE ABLE TO SAVE YOUR DAUGHTER.

32:51.270 --> 32:52.703
[JUDGE]: MR. MORGAN,

32:52.705 --> 32:54.338
I HAVE BEEN CONVINCED THAT
THE RELEVANCE OF THE RULING

32:54.340 --> 32:56.373
ON MATERIAL EVIDENCE FROM 1898

32:56.375 --> 32:57.708
AND I AM GOING TO ALLOW IT.

32:57.710 --> 33:01.011
MOTION DENIED.

33:01.013 --> 33:04.247
I AM NOW PREPARED TO DELIVER
MY RULING ON YOUR APPEAL.

33:04.249 --> 33:06.717
AND AFTER READING THE TRANSCRIPTS FROM YOUR TRIAL,

33:06.719 --> 33:08.452
I AM INCLINED TO AGREE

33:08.454 --> 33:12.322
WITH THE JURY'S ORIGINAL VERDICT OF "GUILTY."

33:14.192 --> 33:17.260
[♪]

33:17.262 --> 33:19.162
[MAN OVER P.A.]:
<i>VISITOR FOR BRACKNER.</i>

33:20.465 --> 33:22.499
[♪]

33:57.402 --> 33:59.603
MY NAME IS MICHAEL WHEELER.

34:03.608 --> 34:06.076
MY WIFE, UM...

34:07.578 --> 34:10.514
MY WIFE...

34:10.516 --> 34:12.516
SHE DIED IN A RIVER-RAFTING ACCIDENT

34:12.518 --> 34:15.218
10 YEARS AGO.

34:15.220 --> 34:17.788
I FOUND A LETTER THAT SHE WROTE,
AND IN IT SHE SAYS THAT YOU...

34:19.824 --> 34:22.192
THAT YOU WERE THE, UH...

34:28.766 --> 34:31.234
[♪]

34:43.448 --> 34:45.415
I DON'T REMEMBER.

34:47.752 --> 34:50.754
PEOPLE'S RELATIVES, THEY SHOW UP EVERY NOW AND THEN,

34:50.756 --> 34:52.355
ASKING QUESTIONS.

34:52.357 --> 34:53.490
MOSTLY "WHY?"

34:53.492 --> 34:55.425
I DIDN'T COME HERE TO ASK WHY.

34:55.427 --> 34:58.428
YOU'VE SEEN THE MONSTER.

34:58.430 --> 35:00.263
SO GO AHEAD

35:00.265 --> 35:02.499
AND TELL ME TO BURN IN HELL, OR YOU FORGIVE ME,

35:02.501 --> 35:04.668
OR YOU DO WHATEVER
YOU'VE GOT TO DO TO GET CLOSURE,

35:04.670 --> 35:06.536
'CAUSE I GOT LUNCH COMING UP, AND IT'S PIZZA DAY.

35:07.672 --> 35:09.272
YOU HAVE A DAUGHTER.

35:13.444 --> 35:16.179
HER NAME'S ABBY.

35:16.181 --> 35:19.316
WHEN SHE WAS 12, SHE WAS IN THE SAME ACCIDENT,

35:19.318 --> 35:21.618
AND NOW SHE...

35:23.187 --> 35:25.122
SHE NEEDS A KIDNEY TRANSPLANT.

35:28.893 --> 35:31.728
[STARTS LAUGHING]

35:32.864 --> 35:34.264
[THUMPS TABLE]

35:34.266 --> 35:35.832
[BRACKNER]:
YOU CAN'T MAKE ME DO THAT.

35:35.834 --> 35:36.900
OF COURSE NOT--

35:36.902 --> 35:38.435
YOU CAN'T EVEN PROVE THAT'S MY KID!

35:38.437 --> 35:39.903
BUT A TEST CAN.

35:39.905 --> 35:41.872
A REALLY SIMPLE TEST.

35:41.874 --> 35:44.875
YEAH, WELL, IT DON'T MATTER.

35:47.879 --> 35:50.647
SHE'S 22 NOW.

35:50.649 --> 35:53.383
SHE'S BEAUTIFUL AND SHE'S SMART AND FUNNY.

35:54.919 --> 35:57.320
SHE HAS BLUE EYES,

35:57.322 --> 35:59.389
AND SHE'S TALL...

35:59.391 --> 36:01.424
LIKE YOU.

36:01.426 --> 36:03.393
[♪]

36:18.442 --> 36:21.878
NOBODY MAKES ME DO NOTHING I DON'T WANNA DO.

36:21.880 --> 36:24.381
THAT'S TRUE.

36:24.383 --> 36:26.349
THAT IS TRUE.

36:32.523 --> 36:34.558
[CHAIRS SCRAPING FLOOR]

36:35.693 --> 36:38.261
YOU HAVE A CHANCE HERE...

36:38.263 --> 36:41.231
TO DO SOMETHING GOOD,
SOMETHING THAT MATTERS.

36:43.234 --> 36:45.635
HOW MANY OTHER GUYS IN HERE GET THAT?

36:48.306 --> 36:49.773
IT'S A SIMPLE TEST.

36:49.775 --> 36:53.276
THEY JUST SCRAPE CELLS
FROM THE INSIDE OF YOUR CHEEK.

36:58.416 --> 37:00.417
[♪]

37:04.255 --> 37:07.224
SHE LOOKS LIKE MY MOTHER.

37:09.260 --> 37:10.760
[QUIET SOB] IS THAT GOOD?

37:13.431 --> 37:16.333
[♪]

37:18.269 --> 37:20.437
[WEEPS]

37:24.542 --> 37:26.776
[♪]

37:50.301 --> 37:51.868
[DOOR THUDS]

37:51.870 --> 37:53.737
[LOCK CLICKS]

37:53.739 --> 37:56.439
[♪]

38:01.412 --> 38:03.747
[EXHALES DEEPLY]

38:06.017 --> 38:08.852
[♪]

38:20.631 --> 38:22.832
DAD! YOU SHAVED.

38:22.834 --> 38:24.501
YEAH. IT WAS TIME.

38:25.569 --> 38:26.736
HEY, HONEY.

38:26.738 --> 38:28.371
I GOT YOUR MESSAGE.

38:28.373 --> 38:29.873
BUT WHY HERE?

38:29.875 --> 38:32.075
UH...

38:34.879 --> 38:36.046
WELL, WE NEED TO TALK.

38:36.048 --> 38:38.815
AND, UH...

38:41.052 --> 38:43.586
I WANTED US ALL TO BE TOGETHER.

38:45.356 --> 38:47.657
OKAY.

38:47.659 --> 38:49.459
[♪]

38:53.464 --> 38:55.799
[BUZZING CHATTER OF CROWD]

39:06.610 --> 39:07.877
[SHANE CHUCKLES]

39:07.879 --> 39:09.079
OLIVER, WHAT DOES IT TAKE

39:09.081 --> 39:10.914
TO GET YOU TO LET YOUR HAIR DOWN

39:10.916 --> 39:12.615
AND LET YOURSELF HAVE A LITTLE FUN?

39:12.617 --> 39:14.718
I WILL CONSIDER HAVING FUN, MS. MCINERNEY,

39:14.720 --> 39:17.087
ONCE MY ENTIRE TEAM IS ASSEMBLED

39:17.089 --> 39:18.822
AND ACCOUNTED FOR.

39:18.824 --> 39:20.090
THAT INCLUDES NORMAN.

39:20.092 --> 39:21.658
HE'S NOT HERE?

39:21.660 --> 39:23.026
THEY'RE ABOUT TO START.

39:23.028 --> 39:24.060
MM.

39:24.062 --> 39:26.363
OH, MY!

39:26.365 --> 39:28.732
[♪]

39:37.541 --> 39:39.442
UH, BARKEEP.

39:39.444 --> 39:40.977
MAY I HAVE AN ARNOLD PALMER?

39:40.979 --> 39:43.713
SHAKEN... NOT STIRRED.

39:43.715 --> 39:46.616
NORMAN, WE WERE GROWING CONCERNED.

39:47.651 --> 39:49.619
AHH. THANK YOU.

39:49.621 --> 39:51.121
I SEE YOU DRESSED FOR THE OCCASION.

39:51.123 --> 39:52.589
AH, YES.

39:52.591 --> 39:54.090
UH, I OFTEN DRESS

39:54.092 --> 39:56.126
FOR OCCASIONS.

39:56.128 --> 39:57.460
[BREATHLESS CHUCKLE]

39:57.462 --> 40:00.563
RITA? MAY I BUY YOU AN ARNOLD PALMER?

40:00.565 --> 40:02.632
WHY, Y-YES.

40:02.634 --> 40:05.535
PLEASE. WITH AN UMBRELLA, PLEASE.

40:06.871 --> 40:08.872
[♪]

40:11.842 --> 40:13.643
I OWE YOU
AN APOLOGY.

40:13.645 --> 40:16.146
I CAN'T IMAGINE WHAT FOR.

40:16.148 --> 40:17.614
WELL, DO YOU REMEMBER THE MORNING

40:17.616 --> 40:19.549
THAT YOU BROUGHT THE LETTER
TO ME AND SHANE?

40:19.551 --> 40:21.017
I DO.

40:21.019 --> 40:22.652
OKAY, WELL, AHEM,

40:22.654 --> 40:23.953
BEFORE YOU WALKED IN,  LET IT SLIP

40:23.955 --> 40:25.522
THAT--

40:25.524 --> 40:27.724
NO, I FLAT-OUT TOLD HER

40:27.726 --> 40:28.958
THAT YOU'D OVERHEARD

40:28.960 --> 40:30.960
OUR CONVERSATION ABOUT YOU THE OTHER WEEK,

40:30.962 --> 40:34.130
BUT I MADE HER PROMISE NOT
TO TELL YOU THAT SHE KNEW--

40:34.132 --> 40:35.532
I KNEW.

40:35.534 --> 40:37.100
I KNOW. APOLOGY ACCEPTED.

40:37.102 --> 40:38.468
THANK YOU.

40:38.470 --> 40:40.770
"AND THE TRUTH SHALL SET YOU FREE."

40:41.872 --> 40:43.473
OH, YEAH?

40:44.875 --> 40:46.943
[REBECCA]:
IN THE THREE HAPPY WEEKS

40:46.945 --> 40:48.645
THAT I HAVE SPENT AT THE DENVER BRANCH

40:48.647 --> 40:49.913
OF THE U.S. POST OFFICE,

40:49.915 --> 40:51.514
I HAVE LEARNED

40:51.516 --> 40:54.751
NOT ONLY WHAT IT MEANS
TO BE A BETTER POSTAL WORKER...

40:54.753 --> 40:56.753
BUT I HAVE LEARNED FROM THESE HONOUREES

40:56.755 --> 40:59.556
WHAT IT MEANS TO BE A <i>PROUD </i> POSTAL WORKER.

41:00.724 --> 41:01.723
IT MAY BE TRUE

41:01.725 --> 41:04.627
THAT ELECTRONIC THOUGHT
HAS TAKEN OVER OUR WORLD...

41:04.629 --> 41:06.896
I MEAN, WE TWEET AND TEXT
FASTER THAN WE CAN THINK.

41:06.898 --> 41:07.931
"O.M.G."

41:07.933 --> 41:09.466
[LAUGHTER]

41:09.468 --> 41:11.901
BUT A YEAR AGO, OR PERHAPS A HUNDRED YEARS AGO,

41:11.903 --> 41:14.771
SOMEONE WROTE A LETTER WITH REAL WORDS

41:14.773 --> 41:17.807
AND MORE THAN TWO SECONDS
OF THOUGHT PUT BEHIND THEM,

41:17.809 --> 41:20.710
AND WE ARE LIVING THEIR FUTURE.

41:20.712 --> 41:22.645
THERE ARE THOUSANDS OF LETTERS,

41:22.647 --> 41:26.749
EACH ONE A VOICE FROM THE PAST,
JUST WAITING TO BE HEARD.

41:26.751 --> 41:28.151
IT'LL TAKE THE KIND OF SACRIFICE

41:28.153 --> 41:30.253
AND DEVOTION GIVEN BY YOU,

41:30.255 --> 41:32.589
THE HONOUREES WHO HAVE EACH RECEIVED

41:32.591 --> 41:34.090
NOT ONLY
THE DISTINGUISHED SERVICE AWARD

41:34.092 --> 41:35.525
FROM THIS BRANCH,

41:35.527 --> 41:37.827
BUT I AM HAPPY TO ANNOUNCE

41:37.829 --> 41:40.797
THAT THE POSTMASTER GENERAL OF THE UNITED STATES...

41:42.166 --> 41:44.934
...HAS INSTRUCTED ME TO CONFER UPON YOU

41:44.936 --> 41:47.770
THE HIGHEST HONOUR FOR ANY U.S. POSTAL WORKER--

41:48.873 --> 41:50.673
"THE DARK OF NIGHT AWARD."

41:50.675 --> 41:51.908
[POSTABLES GASPING]

41:51.910 --> 41:54.277
[CROWD APPLAUDING]

41:55.913 --> 41:57.213
[LAUGHING]

41:57.215 --> 41:59.749
[APPLAUSE CONTINUES]

42:02.820 --> 42:05.855
[♪]

42:10.828 --> 42:13.096
NOW, THIS IS FUN.

42:14.865 --> 42:16.132
[LAUGHING]

42:16.134 --> 42:18.968
[♪]
